    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1538" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀσκέω</span></b> , ipf. 3 sing. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἤσκειν</span> (for <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἤσκεεν</span>), aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἤσκησα</span>,
          perf. pass. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἤσκημαι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">work
            out</span> with skill, aor., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">wrought</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.592</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; χιτῶνα πτύσσειν καὶ ἀσκεῖν</span>, ‘smooth
          out,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 1.439</span></i>; the part., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀσκήσᾱς</span>, is often used for amplification,
          ‘elaborately,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 3.438</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 14.240</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
